DefaultDescription: The shovel is a tool used for digging blocks made of loose materials, such as sand or gravel. It significantly speeds up the digging process, but will eventually be discarded due to severe damage. Shovels made from better materials last longer and dig faster.

The pickaxe is a tool used for quarrying hard blocks like stone or ice. It significantly speeds up the quarrying process, but will eventually be discarded due to severe damage. Pickaxes made from better materials last longer and quarry faster.

The steel axe is a tool used for cutting soft blocks, such as wood, furniture, or leaves. It significantly speeds up the cutting process, but will eventually be discarded due to severe damage. Axes made from better materials last longer and cut faster. The axe is also a powerful weapon, although it can be difficult to hit moving targets.

The rake is a tool for converting dirt into farmland. After the rake turns dirt into farmland, it can be planted. The rake will eventually be discarded due to severe damage. Rakes made from better materials last longer.

The spear is a versatile weapon that can be either thrown or used for melee attacks. With use, it will eventually lose its sharpness and become damaged. Spears made from better materials will last longer and deal more damage. Thrown spears will stick into soft materials. It might be difficult to remove a spear embedded too deeply into a target.

The machete is a simple sword, a slashing weapon very effective for melee attacks. With use, the machete will gradually lose its sharpness and eventually become damaged. Machetes made from better materials will last longer and deal more damage.
The steel hammer is a tool used for quarrying hard blocks like stone or ice. It has the fastest quarrying process, but it will eventually be discarded due to severe damage.
Copper alloy tools can perform similarly to steel tools, but their durability is not as good as steel tools.
